p>2q
\big|\sqrt{2}-\frac{p}{q}\big|>\big|\sqrt{2}-\frac{p}{p}\big|
\frac{p_{n_k}}{q_{n_k}}\not\to\sqrt{2}
 \frac{1}{q_n}\ge\varepsilon, 
 \frac{p_{n_k}}{q_{n_k}}\to\sqrt{2}\quad\text{and}\quad q_n\le\frac{1}{\varepsilon}. 
 q_{n_k}\le\frac{1}{\varepsilon}\quad\Longrightarrow\quad q_{n_k}\in \{1,\ldots,\lfloor\varepsilon^{-1}\rfloor\}, 
 d=\min\left\{\left|\sqrt{2}-\frac{p}{q}\right|: p\in\mathbb N\,\,\text{and}\,\, q\in \{1,\ldots,\lfloor\varepsilon^{-1}\rfloor\}\right\}. 
 d=\min\left\{\left|\sqrt{2}-\frac{p}{q}\right|: q\in \{1,\ldots,\lfloor\varepsilon^{-1}\rfloor\} \,\,\text{and}\,\, p\in\{1,2,\ldots,2q\} \right\}, 
 \left|\frac{p_{n_k}}{q_{n_k}}-\sqrt{2}\right|\ge d. 
